title: Authorities find key clue in Google manager's murder - New York Post
text:
Modal Trigger Vanessa Marcotte AP 
Massachusetts investigators have DNA of the man suspected of killing a New York City woman , slain in the Bay State this past summer, officials said Thursday. 
Police are looking for a Latino man in connection to the murder of Vanessa Marcotte, who was killed Aug. 7 while visiting her mother in Princeton, a small town in central Massachusetts about 17 miles north of Worcester, prosecutors said. 
“We feel this DNA is from our person of interest.” said Worcester DA Joseph Early said. 
The prosecutor declined to reveal how or where investigators found the suspect’s DNA. 
“We want to do everything we can to find this killer,” Early added. 
The 27-year-old Marcotte was found in nearby woods about a half-mile from her mom’s house. 
Marcotte grew up in Leominster and had been working as an account manager for Mountain View, California-based Google in New York. Share this:
